{
  "stem": "26792.5",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We went back to Riga.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And immediately, the KGB started hunting us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were-- I got married on the 27th of August, 1945.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And only for one simple reason.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because Latvian people-- all non-Jewish people, actually, believed that if one marries, in the Soviet Union, a Jewish, or a Jew, his life is saved, that they're very-- the Jewish people have a lot to say in the country, and it's-- which is not true.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "May.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I'm staying.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm going to Goldingen to see what's happening there in my shtetel, and I found [? that ?] [? going ?] [? on ?] living in my house, and all our furniture, all our things.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they didn't-- they didn't want to-- even to hear anything about the apartment.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we went to the Jewish cemetery again and wanted to see whether the graves still exist.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we saw there is no staying in Goldingen anymore, that we have to go back to Riga.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We-- we understood that we are lost people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Everybody was dead.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I went back to college-- which was not a college anymore, which was an institute of the English language-- in order to pass my final examinations, which I hadn't passed.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So, while--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Mm, well, she was all right.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was in the countryside.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I came to Riga, she came to stay with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were wanted.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were kept in the KGB for days and nights and asked questions about people whom we had never seen and never heard of.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They never incriminated us anything we have done during the time of the German occupation, because they knew exactly that this is [? kosher. ?]",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My friend went to testify for [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He said, yeah.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
